<h1>Diagram 1 — System Architecture</h1>

<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>
  Shows the logical application architecture: how the employee browser interacts with the
  Vercel-hosted frontend, the FastAPI backend, Supabase (Auth, PostgreSQL, Storage), and
  the Redis/Celery background job layer. Highlights the security boundary that prevents
  the browser from ever receiving the Supabase service-role key.
</p>

<h2>Mermaid Source</h2>
<pre>
flowchart LR
    U[("👤 Employee Browser")] --> W["Vercel\nNext.js Frontend\nerp-dusky-six.vercel.app"]
    W --> A["FastAPI Backend API\napi.prathlabs.com"]

    A --> AUTH["Supabase Auth\n(JWT validation, PKCE OAuth)"]
    A --> DB[("Supabase PostgreSQL\n(source of truth, RLS enabled)")]
    A --> ST[("Supabase Storage\n(private buckets, signed URLs)")]
    A --> R[("Redis\n(job broker, rate-limit state)")]
    R --> C["Celery Worker\n+ Scheduler"]
    C --> DB
    C --> ST

    W -. "public anon config only\n(no service-role key)" .-> AUTH
    A -. "service-role\nserver-side only" .-> DB
    A -. "signed URLs\n(short-lived)" .-> ST

    style U fill:#E8F4FD,stroke:#2E6DA4
    style W fill:#D6EAF8,stroke:#2E6DA4
    style A fill:#D5E8D4,stroke:#27AE60
    style DB fill:#FFF3CD,stroke:#F39C12
    style ST fill:#FFF3CD,stroke:#F39C12
    style AUTH fill:#FFF3CD,stroke:#F39C12
    style R fill:#FADBD8,stroke:#E74C3C
    style C fill:#FADBD8,stroke:#E74C3C
</pre>

<h2>Key Points</h2>
<ul>
  <li>The browser communicates only with the Vercel frontend and the FastAPI API — never directly with the database or private Storage buckets.</li>
  <li>The Supabase service-role key exists only on the FastAPI server and is never exposed to any client bundle.</li>
  <li>All sensitive writes (document upload, checkout, approval, attendance correction) go through FastAPI, which enforces RBAC/ABAC and writes immutable audit events.</li>
  <li>Supabase Storage buckets are private; all file access goes through short-lived signed URLs generated by FastAPI after authorization.</li>
  <li>Redis acts as the Celery job broker for asynchronous archive ZIP generation and scheduled jobs (e.g., export expiration); it is not directly reachable from the browser or frontend.</li>
</ul>

