<h1>Diagram 3 — Authentication Flow</h1>

<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>
  Shows the complete Google OAuth login sequence using PKCE, how the Supabase JWT
  reaches FastAPI, and how FastAPI resolves and validates the employee identity before
  granting access.
</p>

<h2>Mermaid Source</h2>
<pre>
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as 👤 User
    participant Web as Next.js Frontend
    participant Supa as Supabase Auth
    participant Google as Google OAuth
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant DB as Supabase PostgreSQL

    User->>Web: Click "Sign in with Google"
    Web->>Web: Server-side: generate PKCE code_verifier
    Web->>Web: Store code_verifier in HTTP-only cookie
    Web->>Supa: Redirect to OAuth authorize endpoint
    Supa->>Google: Forward to Google OAuth consent
    Google-->>Supa: Authorization code (verified identity)
    Supa->>Supa: Exchange code for session using code_verifier
    Supa-->>Web: Supabase session + signed JWT
    Web->>Web: Store session (not in localStorage)

    Note over Web,API: Every subsequent API request

    Web->>API: Request with Authorization: Bearer JWT
    API->>Supa: Fetch JWKS (public keys, cached)
    API->>API: Validate: signature, issuer, audience, expiry
    API->>API: Check email domain (@iemsnewdelhi.com)
    API->>DB: Resolve user_account + employee record
    API->>API: Check employee status = ACTIVE
    API-->>Web: 200 OK (or 401/403 if denied)
</pre>

<h2>Key Points</h2>
<ul>
  <li>PKCE (Proof Key for Code Exchange) is implemented server-side in Next.js: the code verifier is stored in a server-set cookie before the OAuth redirect, preventing token interception via browser state.</li>
  <li>Only email addresses from the @iemsnewdelhi.com domain are accepted; any other domain receives 403 EMAIL_DOMAIN_NOT_ALLOWED even with a valid Google account.</li>
  <li>FastAPI validates the JWT using Supabase's JWKS endpoint (asymmetric key validation); it checks signature, issuer, audience, and expiry on every request — no session state is maintained on the server.</li>
  <li>If an employee account is deactivated in the system, they receive 403 on all requests even with a valid Supabase session.</li>
  <li>The Director account (director@iemsnewdelhi.com) is resolved as a Super User, granting elevated access to the Director Dashboard and all admin functions.</li>
</ul>

<div class="evidence">
  <strong>Evidence files:</strong>
  docs/04_SECURITY_MODEL.md &nbsp;|&nbsp; apps/api/app/core/auth.py &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  apps/api/app/api/v1/me.py &nbsp;|&nbsp; apps/web/src/lib/api.ts &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  apps/web/src/app/auth/signin/route.ts &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  apps/web/src/app/auth/callback/route.ts &nbsp;|&nbsp; CHANGELOG.md
</div>

