<h1>Diagram 4 — Authorization Flow</h1>

<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>
  Shows the complete backend authorization pipeline for every protected API request,
  from JWT validation through RBAC and ABAC checks to the immutable audit event write.
</p>

<h2>Mermaid Source</h2>
<pre>
flowchart TD
    Req["Incoming API Request\nAuthorization: Bearer JWT"] --> JWT["Validate JWT\n(signature, issuer, audience, expiry)"]
    JWT --> Emp["Resolve user_account + employee\nfrom Supabase PostgreSQL"]
    Emp --> Active{"Employee\nstatus = ACTIVE?"}
    Active -- No --> Deny["401 / 403 Denied\n(EMPLOYEE_NOT_FOUND or\nEMAIL_DOMAIN_NOT_ALLOWED)"]
    Active -- Yes --> RBAC["RBAC permission check\ne.g. project.view, document.upload,\nattendance.correct, approval.approve"]
    RBAC --> HasPerm{"Permission\ngranted?"}
    HasPerm -- No --> SU{"Is Super User?"}
    SU -- No --> Deny
    SU -- Yes --> Reason{"Override reason\nprovided?"}
    Reason -- No --> Deny
    Reason -- Yes --> ABAC
    HasPerm -- Yes --> ABAC["ABAC context check\ne.g. project membership,\ndepartment, confidentiality,\nresource state"]
    ABAC --> ABACPass{"ABAC\npasses?"}
    ABACPass -- No --> Deny
    ABACPass -- Yes --> DB["Execute DB operation\n(service-role RPC / transaction)"]
    DB --> Audit["Write immutable audit event\n(actor, action, resource, timestamp)"]
    Audit --> Resp["Return API response\n200 / 201 / 204"]

    style Deny fill:#FADBD8,stroke:#E74C3C
    style Resp fill:#D5E8D4,stroke:#27AE60
    style Audit fill:#FFF3CD,stroke:#F39C12
</pre>

<h2>RBAC Permission Examples</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Permission</th><th>Who holds it</th><th>What it controls</th></tr>
  <tr><td>project.view</td><td>Employee, Manager, Admin, Director</td><td>View project list and details</td></tr>
  <tr><td>document.upload</td><td>Manager, Admin</td><td>Upload documents to folders</td></tr>
  <tr><td>attendance.correct</td><td>Admin, Super Admin</td><td>Correct employee attendance sessions</td></tr>
  <tr><td>approval.approve</td><td>Manager, Admin, Director</td><td>Approve or reject approval requests</td></tr>
  <tr><td>audit.view</td><td>Admin, Super Admin, Director</td><td>Access full audit event log</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Key Points</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Authorization is enforced independently by FastAPI on every request; frontend route guards are UX-only and provide no security guarantee.</li>
  <li>The ABAC layer checks contextual attributes such as project membership, document confidentiality level, resource state, and department — providing finer-grained control than role alone.</li>
  <li>Super User overrides bypass RBAC/ABAC restrictions but require a meaningful reason string sent via the X-IEMS-Override-Reason header, which is stored in the immutable audit log.</li>
  <li>All database writes for sensitive operations use service-role-only Supabase RPCs executed inside transactions, ensuring atomicity between the business operation and the audit event write.</li>
  <li>Supabase RLS acts as a defense-in-depth layer at the database level, independent of application-layer authorization.</li>
</ul>

<div class="evidence">
  <strong>Evidence files:</strong>
  docs/04_SECURITY_MODEL.md &nbsp;|&nbsp; apps/api/app/core/auth.py &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  apps/api/app/core/permissions.py &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  apps/api/app/api/dependencies.py &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  apps/api/app/services/*.py &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  supabase/migrations/*rls*.sql &nbsp;|&nbsp; supabase/migrations/*audit*.sql
</div>

