<h1>Diagram 9 — Security Controls Diagram</h1>

<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>
  Shows all security controls layered across the system: browser, API, database,
  Storage, Docker infrastructure, and operations.
</p>

<h2>Mermaid Source</h2>
<pre>
flowchart TB
    subgraph Browser ["Browser Layer"]
        B1["No service-role secrets\nin client bundle"]
        B2["Protected routes\n(UX only — not authorization)"]
        B3["Module hiding UX\n(disabled modules hidden from nav)"]
        B4["Auth tokens not in localStorage"]
    end

    subgraph API ["API Layer (FastAPI)"]
        A1["JWT validation\n(signature, issuer, audience, expiry)"]
        A2["RBAC permission checks"]
        A3["ABAC context checks\n(project, department, resource state)"]
        A4["Redis-backed rate limiting\n(429 RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED)"]
        A5["Security headers\n(nosniff, DENY framing, no-referrer,\npermissions policy, COOP, CSP)"]
        A6["Stable error envelope\n+ X-Request-ID on every response"]
        A7["Immutable audit logging\n(every sensitive operation)"]
        A8["API docs disabled\nin production"]
    end

    subgraph Database ["Database Layer (Supabase PostgreSQL)"]
        D1["RLS on all tables\n(default deny)"]
        D2["Constraints\n(check, unique, FK)"]
        D3["Private schemas\n(app_private, not exposed via PostgREST)"]
        D4["Immutable audit table\n(no UPDATE/DELETE triggers)"]
        D5["Indexes for\nperformance + correctness"]
    end

    subgraph Storage ["Storage Layer (Supabase Storage)"]
        S1["Private buckets\n(no public access)"]
        S2["Signed URLs\n(short-lived, generated by API)"]
        S3["Server-side MIME/size checks\nbefore upload"]
        S4["Immutable storage keys\n(no overwrite)"]
    end

    subgraph Infra ["Docker / Infrastructure Layer"]
        I1["Non-root containers\n(UID 10001)"]
        I2["Redis password\nenforced"]
        I3["Redis on internal\nDocker network only"]
        I4["Caddy admin API\ndisabled in production"]
        I5["no-new-privileges\nconfigured"]
        I6["Resource limits\non all containers"]
        I7["Image scans\n(Docker Scout: 0C/0H on all images)"]
        I8["_FILE secret mounts\nfor service-role key + JWT secret"]
    end

    subgraph Ops ["Operations Layer"]
        O1["Uptime Kuma\n(self-hosted, Raspberry Pi)"]
        O2["UptimeRobot\n(redundant public monitor)"]
        O3["Cloudflare Tunnel\nalerts"]
        O4["Dozzle\n(live container logs)"]
        O5["Rollback runbook\n+ incident response docs"]
        O6["pip-audit\nin backend CI"]
    end

    Browser --> API
    API --> Database
    API --> Storage
    API --> Infra
    Infra --> Ops
</pre>

<h2>Key Points</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Security is layered: a bypass at the browser layer (e.g., direct URL navigation) is blocked by the API layer; a bypass at the API layer is blocked by the database RLS layer.</li>
  <li>The Supabase service-role key is handled exclusively by FastAPI and is never included in any build argument, client bundle, or environment variable accessible to the frontend.</li>
  <li>All Docker images pass Docker Scout vulnerability scanning at 0 critical and 0 high findings; the Caddy image is source-compiled to eliminate CVEs present in the official caddy:2-alpine image.</li>
  <li>Rate limiting uses Redis-backed shared state across all API workers, ensuring limits are enforced consistently even under concurrent requests.</li>
  <li>An immutable audit table (protected by database triggers that block UPDATE and DELETE) provides a tamper-evident record of all sensitive operations.</li>
</ul>

